’s far hum, and the Aerie’s high kites will feel far away in that wet labyrinth where frogs toll and reeds whisper, but the city lives or coughs on what is decided there. You came to repay a breath debt and to return a voice swallowed by cunning water; you may leave owing a price you can carry, or owing a silence you cannot bear. In the Fen, the wind does not lie, but it asks hard truths for the right to pass.\",\n      \"objectives\": [\"Escort Nyssar Fenquill through the reed labyrinth to the Fen Queen’s court.\", \"Track the reed hymn to its source and gather three fenfruits for the offering.\", \"Confront the breath-thief parasite and recover the envoy’s voice in a glass ampule.\", \"Bargain with the Fen Queen for release of the envoy’s breath without triggering the full price of Rogan’s broken wording.\", \"Return the voice to the envoy and secure renewed trade with Whisper Fen healers.\"],\n      \"dialogue\": [\n        {\"speaker\": \"Nyssar Fenquill\", \"lines\": \"Rogan, I remember the day you traded your breath for a moment and stretched a promise until it covered children like shadecloth, and I have never faulted a man for making shade in a killing heat. The Fen, however, counts differently than you and I, and it keeps its ledger in every ripple and reed-bruise and frog note that calls at dusk. A hymn has slipped its leash, taken to the channels like a smuggler, and now it sings in voices the hearer trusts until the throat opens and the words are stolen clean. Three fenfruits will begin the apology, ripe and heavy with the sweet medicine that tastes like a childhood summer cooled under a dripping eave, and then we will walk where lanterns lie and tie knots that do not slip. Stay close to me when the mist thickens, lift your sabre only when the water shivers wrong, and when the Queen asks for a song, give her the whole crack in your voice instead of a pretty shard.\"},\n        {\"speaker\": \"Fen Queen\", \"lines\": \"I know your name, Rogan Kettlebone, 